# C-LOC — 500 Line-of-Code Cap

**Non-negotiable.** No source file in this repo may exceed **500 lines**. CI runs `pnpm run loc-check` (via `scripts/loc-check.mjs`) and **fails the build** on any violation. Honor exclusions listed in `.loc-ignore` only when that file exists and the path is explicitly listed there.

## Rule

- Count physical lines in each file (including blanks and comments) unless excluded by `.loc-ignore`.
- **Hard limit: 500 lines.** There is no grace buffer in CI.
- **Soft limit: ~400 lines.** If a file you are editing approaches 400 lines, split it proactively before adding more logic.
- Orchestrator/shell files should stay **≤200 LOC** (e.g. `step-one-form.tsx`, `step-two-renderer.tsx`, `intake-review.tsx`). Push UI and logic into sibling slice files.

## When to split

| Situation | Split strategy |
|---|---|
| Route handler growing large | Extract Zod schemas, DB queries, and helpers into `lib/` slice files; keep `route.ts` thin |
| Component with many sub-screens | One file per screen (see C-SLICE); orchestrator only wires navigation |
| Test file approaching cap | Split fixtures to `fixtures/`; group tests by behavior in separate `*.test.ts` files |
| Worker/pipeline logic | One processor per file under `workers/transcription/processors/` |

## Agent workflow

1. Before finishing any task, mentally estimate final line count of touched files.
2. If adding code would push a file past 400 lines, **split first**, then implement.
3. Never "just add a few more helpers" to a 450-line file — extract a new slice file instead.
4. At phase boundaries, search for files over 400 LOC and split any that are trending toward the gate.

## Violations (examples)

```tsx
// BAD — monolithic step-one-form.tsx with all four screens inline (~600 lines)
// BAD — stuffing 15 API helpers into a single route.ts
// BAD — one giant *.test.ts mirroring an oversized source file
```

```tsx
// GOOD — step-one-form.tsx (~150 lines) imports about-you, why-here, symptoms, lifestyle-snapshot
// GOOD — route.ts delegates to lib/intake/merge-intake.ts and lib/audit/write-audit.ts
```

## Failure modes (do not do these)

1. **Inlining a whole feature** into an existing file because "it's only 80 more lines" when the file is already at 430 lines.
2. **Generating large boilerplate blocks** (repeated form fields, table-driven UI) in one file instead of extracting shared primitives to `components/ui/`.
3. **Leaving generated migration SQL or lockfiles** out of `.loc-ignore` while counting application source — only ignore paths explicitly listed in `.loc-ignore`; do not add broad ignores to dodge the gate.
4. **Deferring the split** with a `// TODO: split later` comment — CI will fail before "later" arrives.
